s=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eif\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eisset\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nv\"\u003e$_GET\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;_wpnonce\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e])\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e\u0026amp;\u0026amp;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003ewp_verify_nonce\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e...\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;license_envato_switch_tab\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e))\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe reason the CVE is labeled \u003cstrong\u003eUnauthenticated\u003c/strong\u003e is that an attacker does not need an account on the target site to exploit it. A common technique is to trick an admin (or a privileged user) into visiting a page containing the payload. When the admin opens that page, the browser sends a request to the WordPress site including the admin session cookie — so the request is considered authenticated as the admin. If the plugin accepts and executes the parameter without nonce or permission checks, the LFI payload will be processed and exploited.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col start=\"3\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNormalize and validate paths using \u003ca href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.realpath.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003erealpath()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-open show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    t